comments.body:
> I disagree, if you have more than 32 marked frames in flight you are already on very thin ice. The way to solve that is to just not stash new frames (or at least reduce the rate of them) until you receive feedback for the pending data.

@sprangerik I can imagine the encoder wanting to mark new frames as LTR and solicit acks for them even if the previous one have not been acknowledged in the spirit of having as recent a frame as possible as reference in case of loss. Encoder should be free to drop older unacknowledged frames from its buffers. 

It would be good to set up a call with shrim27 to discuss this topic
